				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hi all. I would just like to comment on the frequent questions asked about bards and soloing. Bards are good at soloing but takes a lot of knowledge to do it. First of all I also start off by singing a slow and rooting them and hastning my speed. Than I put on a regen and cast a sheild on myself. If he breaks the root dont worry theres enough time to root again if he is slowed. I than poison him and cast a dot or two i recommend using a dot that can slow the target down and does a steady amount of damage overtime and than nuking him. Than repeat and run around and keep nuking.When song breaks you can heal the damage he's caused if any and use any song to paralyze or stun him if your in a group have the mage or necro stun if not it doesent matter after that just meelee him intill the beast dies. This method will work and once you perfect it, it will work nice indeed. BTW if anyone wants to join my guild SD we are now accepting new members level 40^. Anyways I just acheived the hardest part for my epic! I hope soon I can get this thing. Bards are one of the best soloing classes in the game in my opinion. Well I must be going I have schoolwork to be doing:( Freshman in college, I'll never get used to it but yet I don't think I'll ever want to leave:P<BR>
<BR>
Isthamae Cantane<BR>
Bard of the 42nd missed note<BR>

