			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I would just like to comment a little bit on twinking your bards. I've read several posts here that keep warning people to not twink their bard because it gives everyone a bad name. I have to disagree with this. One point I'm making is that every class has twinks running around the game, so no one can point the finger at bards in general. Now, for the main point of my post. I just started a bard and decided to make it my main. So, at around level 11 I went to East Commonlands (which is the bazaar zone on Quellious) to buy/sell and get a few items. Well, at level 12, I have a full set of Lambent (although I don't really wear all of it), Sainy's Claw, Fiery Blade of Lamentation, and a Smoldering Brand to get my 1hb up. And I also have a good amount of money in the bank to work on my Jewel Crafting skill. Most people figure that I have a higher level character that bought all of the items for my bard, but I made the money and bought the items with the money that I made buying and selling in EC. I see nothing wrong with this. Good armor and weapons means that you're a better character (not necessarily player). It helps you to deal out more damage and to take less hits. I wanted my main character to be the best she could, and I did this by giving her armor that is much higher than her level. Sure, sometimes it makes me sick to see a level 2 Enchanter running around with a Froglok Bonecaster Robe, Glowing Black Stone, and all of the really higher level items, but that is just because, I think, that I'm jealous for not having the means to buy those higher level things for myself. When it comes to twinking, I'd rather someone not go on their higher level characters and give the lower ones items and money, but if you save and make the money (as I did by bartering), then I figure you earned it (I have had to miss out on valuable leveling time to gain the items that I have). Well, anyway, that's my 2cp on twinking.<BR>
<BR>
Divaa<BR>
Bard of 12 songs<BR>
Quellious
				</font>
			</td>

