	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I had a Human Bard in Qeynos and I know of a really useful quest that will raise your faction standing with your guild up to 'warmly'.  And the best thing is you don't even have to be a Bard to do this quest (you would want high faction standing so you could sell things for top dollar :) Here is what you do... Go talk to the guy who is standing outside the guild to the left of the door.  Hail him and talk to him until he gives you a note.  He will ask you to bring it to someone at the docks and then bring back a report.  Take the note and go to the docks.  There is usually one of the people he told you to bring it to standing there.  If not, walk over to the other dock and one of them should be there.  Give it to him.  He will give you a note to take back.  Take it back and give it to the first guy who gave you the note.  He will give you between 6 cp and 2 gp and you will get faction.  Keep doing this, coning him every time you return to see your faction standing.  Do this until the cons 'warmly'.  Also, when he tells you to give the note to one of two guys, talk to them because one of them has a quest  for you that will get you a piece of armor that resists cold.  Thats about it.  This quest is good for newbies who need some money and faction.  Have fun!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
